See AGENTS.md and docs/ for full project guidance.

TL;DR:
- Next.js 16 (App Router, React 19) + Drizzle + Neon Postgres on Vercel.
- TDD is the default. Write a failing test in tests/ first, then implement.
  Never commit with red tests. Precommit hook enforces it.
- Keep README.md in sync with code in the SAME commit when the change
  affects the pitch, stack, scripts, "Shipped", or roadmap.
- Don't reintroduce Supabase.
- No "what" comments — only "why", when non-obvious.
- Tests live in tests/, never co-located. Run with `npm test`.
- Verify with: npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm test && npm run build
- User-facing copy is Russian; code/docs are English.
